---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
// Privacy Policy per PRD Addendum section 4.1
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy â€” Projexions"
  description="Privacy Policy for Projexions website."
  currentPath="/privacy-policy"
>
  <div class="page-container">
    <h1 class="serif-heading text-4xl font-semibold mb-6 text-center">Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed mb-8 text-center">How we collect, use, and protect your information.</p>

    <div class="prose-content">
      <p class="text-lg mb-6"><strong>Last updated:</strong> January 13, 2026</p>

      <section class="mb-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">Information We Collect</h2>
        <p class="mb-4">
          We collect information that you provide directly to us, including when you:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc mb-4">
          <li>Fill out a contact form</li>
          <li>Request a resource</li>
          <li>Subscribe to email updates</li>
          <li>Purchase a product</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mb-4">
          This information may include your name, email address, company name, and other information you choose to provide.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">Email Capture</h2>
        <p class="mb-4">
          When you request a resource or subscribe to updates, we collect your email address. We use this information
          to send you the requested content and, with your consent, to send you updates about our services and content.
        </p>
        <p class="mb-4">
          You can unsubscribe from email communications at any time by clicking the unsubscribe link in any email we send.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">Analytics</h2>
        <p class="mb-4">
          We use analytics tools to understand how visitors interact with our website. This information helps us improve
          our site and services. Analytics data is collected anonymously and does not personally identify you.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">Payment Processors</h2>
        <p class="mb-4">
          For product purchases, we use third-party payment processors (such as Stripe). These processors collect
          and handle payment information according to their own privacy policies. We do not store your payment
          card information on our servers.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">Data Security</h2>
        <p class="mb-4">
          We take reasonable measures to protect the information we collect. However, no method of transmission
          over the internet is 100% secure, and we cannot guarantee absolute security.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">Your Rights (GDPR)</h2>
        <p class="mb-4">
          If you are located in the European Economic Area (EEA), you have certain data protection rights under GDPR:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc mb-4">
          <li>Right to access your personal data</li>
          <li>Right to correct inaccurate data</li>
          <li>Right to delete your data</li>
          <li>Right to restrict processing</li>
          <li>Right to data portability</li>
          <li>Right to object to processing</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mb-4">
          To exercise any of these rights, please contact us through our <a href="/contact" class="text-brand-green no-underline">contact page</a>.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">Contact Us</h2>
        <p class="mb-4">
          If you have questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact us through our <a href="/contact" class="text-brand-green no-underline">contact page</a>.
        </p>
      </section>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
